snippet.textDisplay: Hello all you Billie fans. This sixty-plus musician is right there with you. I think she is a precocious, profound, profane, punk Mozart and I envy you Gen Zs your passion and your emotional engagement. But I'm not here just to praise Billie, but to urge all you fans not to respond to trolls. When you engage with these low-lifes you feed their hollow souls. They love sites visited by passionate fans. They can throw their spleen grenades into a crowded room and wait hungrily for mayhem to ensue. Let me be clear, someone who in a civil, non-demeaning way argues that Ariana should have won best album at the grammys is not a troll -- by all means go back and forth on this and have fun. On the other hand, someone who types in that Billie is trailer-trash who sleeps with her brother is a grade A troll.  You must understand that no matter how skillful, eloquent or witty your put down, when you engage with these people you are providing blood to these anemic vampires -- they win.  I have a theory (completely unsubstantiated) that most of this stuff comes from 48-year-old male losers living in their mothers' basements and working at the car wash. After all anyone can create a bogus public handle on the web.  Not responding is the best way to ensure that these people have no recourse but to stew in their own spiteful juices and stay trapped in their barren, joyless lives. Please don't feed the trolls.
